result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Order Granting Stip to Bond Mod
No contact with Menards or Kwik Trip Stores in Douglas County.

3:04 PM Defendant Logen Scott Hunker in court.  Attorney Angela Wilson in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Attorney/defendant acknowledges receipt of criminal complaint, waives reading. Defendant's address confirmed. 
Court recites charges against defendant and possible penalties. 
Defendant advised of right to consult an attorney.  
Defendant pleads guilty; Court accepts plea, knowing and voluntary.
Court quashes warrant; questions non appearance.
Defendant states his copy of bail receipt said court was at 2:30
State has copy of bail receipt and indicates that it has todays date at 1:30pm.
Notes no history and was going to request a sb but now that there was a non appearance and a warrant was issued.
Court questions defendant on ability to post cash.
State reviews charges in complaint and  combined with the non appearance requests $250cb with conditions of No contact with Kwik Trip Stores in Douglas County and Menards.
Court questions defendant if he can post the cash; he indicates he can call someone close to bring the cash.
Court orders $250 cash bail No contact with Menards or Kwik Trip Stores in Douglas County.
Court informs defendant about the waiver of attorney form.
Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for November 22, 2022 at 11:00 am.
2:05 PM Defendant Logen Scott Hunker not in court.  Attorney Allison Cogbill in court for State of Wisconsin.  Court calls case. State request warrant, statewide. Court orders warrant.
